#############################################################
#   Unofficial Japanese language pack for Jolla
#   Takahiro HASHIMOTO <kenya888@gmail.com>
#############################################################

 Contents: 

 1. Prerequisite
 2. How to create rpm for Japanese translation
 3. How to create rpm for another language

#############################################################
1. Prerequisite
#############################################################

You need to setup Linux PC with capability of making rpm(rpmbuild).
I confirm on Fedora 20 and Gentoo Linux (both are x86_64)

 
#############################################################
2. How to create rpm for Japanese translation
#############################################################

If you want to create Japanese language package, just run

 sh createall.sh

If you want to fetch the latest of latest ts files from Transifex, run

 sh createall.sh -f

You can find rpm/srpm packages in rpmbuild directroy

#############################################################
3. How to create rpm for another language
#############################################################

Tools are ready for creating package of another language with some preparation.
 
First, prepare your lang setting file like the one in
usr/share/jolla-supported-languages/ja.conf
(i.e. usr/share/jolla-supported-languages/cs.conf (Czech))

Second, prepare the spec file that create rpm for your language like
rpm/unofficial-jolla-language-pack-ja.spec
(i.e. rpm/unofficial-jolla-language-pack-cs (Czech))

Are you ready? So set TSLANG variable and run, for example Czech

  TSLANG=cs sh createall.sh -f

Of cource ts files should be created on Transifex 
"unofficial-jolla-translations" project.

https://www.transifex.com/projects/p/unofficial-jolla-translations/

If all are done, you can find the packages for your language on rpmbuild directory.
